    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/3–2146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 21, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2740. For Gallman from the Secretary. Please convey following message to Bevin
                    from me: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Much disturbed by your recent note. I intend to insist on serious
                            consideration of Iran question at forthcoming meeting of the Security
                            Council. I will attend meeting on behalf of our Government. I regret you
                            do not plan to come because issue is necessarily critical and may affect
                            whole future of United Nations. I should not favor any meeting at Paris
                            which would indicate in advance that final disposition of Iran question
                            was to be delayed. I intend to insist on final disposition now.</p>
                        <p>“I do not, however, think that we should delay action on proposed meeting
                            of the Council of Foreign Ministers to complete drafts of peace
                            treaties. It should be helpful to indicate in this way that we expect a
                            favorable disposition of Iran issue. But Paris meeting should be called
                            on the assumption that we are going to concentrate on peace treaties so
                            that Peace Conference when it convenes on May 1 will have something
                            tangible to consider.</p>
                        <pb facs="0052" n="34" xml:id="pg_34"/>
                        <p>“I should like to send not later than Saturday my proposed message
                            suggesting the meeting of the Council of Foreign Ministers at Paris on
                            April 25 instead of April 15. I hope that you will have no serious
                            objection to my so doing.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
